HEADWORD: Elasipoda
<hw>El`a*sip"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ metal beaten out, metal plate + <ets>-poda</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>An order of holothurians mostly found in the
deep sea. They are remarkable for their bilateral symmetry and curious
forms.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Elasmopoda</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

